                        cell.configure(with: ["Trim Your Hair Beard and Nails Regularly", "Try Skin Care", "Get Your Shirts and Suits Tailored", "Wear a Tie Whenever You Can", "Always Smell Good", "Make Sure Everything You Own is Quality and Classy", "Workout", "Try out Some Sunglasses"], with: ["Basically, keep it clean. It’s a scientifically proven fact that girls like facial hair. They find stubble very attractive, to be more specific. So ditch your razor and start using a trimmer for a neater finish. Much like your facial hair, your head says a lot about your habits. Being consistent with your haircuts doesn’t just show that you care about yourself but also keeps your mane from looking rough and untidy. The same theory is valid for your nails. You don’t have to go get a manicure but keep them short and neat.",
                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         "Whether to make our skin age like a raisin or a fine wine, the choice is ours. But to achieve the latter, a good skincare routine is a must. And we’re not just talking about your face here but also your hands and feet. While you’re working on your skin make sure to conceal your dark spots, undereye circles and blemishes using the makeup essentials for men. It’s super quick and easy.",
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         "The quality of the fabric of your clothes is very important and so is their colour. But the biggest secret weapon of menswear is fine tailoring. Everything from your T-shirts to your trousers should fit you comfortably—neither too baggy nor too tight. As for the fabrics and shades, pick the ones with less shine in timeless colours like blacks, blues, beiges, greys and whites. It’s easier to style them.",                                                       "Gone are the days when workplaces or events used to impose a formal dress code. It’s all cool and casual now which makes it easier for anyone wearing formals to stand out. You don’t have to wear a suit every day but a tie and a nice belt will only add to your attractiveness.",
                                                                                                                                              "When you smell good you don’t have to make much effort to make an impression. Good fragrances do half the work for you. Just pick your personal favourite and you’re good to go!",
                                                                                                                                              "Be it leather shoes, a finely-crafted watch, or your earbuds, when you choose quality over quantity, it shows and vice versa. Shop with a mindset that you deserve the comfort and fit of everything that’s mindfully designed.It’s okay to have less of each but make sure you wear good quality leather and use tech accessories loaded with the latest features and design. Keep your Oxford, Brogues and Derbys polished. Shinier shoes have confidence written all over them.",
                                                                               
                                                                                                                                              "In the long run, workout. Not necessarily to lose weight but to tone up your muscles. Improve your posture. Even the best outfit and grooming tricks cannot save your look if your body language doesn’t convey confidence. Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, keep your back straight, your chest out and your arms open. Lastly, be kind, spread good vibes and smile as often as you can. It makes you more attractive, instantly.",
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         "Taking care of your eyes and the skin around them is a very important step. The area under your eyes ages more quickly than any other part of your skin. To prevent that, continue using a sunscreen every time you go out, start using under eye gels and schedule an eye exam. Because when you can’t see properly, you squint which deepens frown lines and crow’s feet. As a faster alternative and for more protection, swap your thinly rimmed aviators for oversized frames."], with: ["https://thumbs.dreamstime.com/b/stylish-handsome-men-17503604.jpg", "https://thumbs.dreamstime.com/b/stylish-handsome-men-17503604.jpg", "https://thumbs.dreamstime.com/b/stylish-handsome-men-17503604.jpg", "https://thumbs.dreamstime.com/b/stylish-handsome-men-17503604.jpg", "https://thumbs.dreamstime.com/b/stylish-handsome-men-17503604.jpg", "https://thumbs.dreamstime.com/b/stylish-handsome-men-17503604.jpg", "https://thumbs.dreamstime.com/b/stylish-handsome-men-17503604.jpg", "https://thumbs.dreamstime.com/b/stylish-handsome-men-17503604.jpg"])
                
