                                                                                                                                            "Mondragon, in Spain, is one of the most sucessful democratically run corporations in the world. Worker cooperatives are values-driven businesses that put worker and community benefit at the core of their purpose. In contrast to traditional companies, worker members at worker cooperatives participate in the profits, oversight, and often management of the enterprise using democratic practices. The two central characteristics of worker cooperatives are: Worker members own the business and they participate in its financial success on the basis of their labor contribution to the cooperative. Worker members have representation on and vote for the board of directors or governing body, adhering to the principle of one worker, one vote. (US Federation of Worker Cooperatives).",
                                                                        
